http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/35-hurt-as-bus-overturns/article14011924.ece

At least 35 persons, including 22 women, were injured as a bus overturned at the Thekkil ghat section of the National Highway near Chattamchal, some 10 km from here on Wednesday.The mishap occurred around 9 a.m. when the driver of the packed private bus plying on the Kanhangad-Kasaragod route lost control of the vehicle and hit a truck in the rear before turning turtle, the police said.The passengers trapped inside the bus were extricated by the Vidyanagar Police, Fire and Rescue Services personnel assisted by the local residents, they said.The injured, most of them students of various educational institutions in Kasaragod, were being treated at various hospitals in the town.